  "prompt": "Why doesn't Wetransfer give the shared file links immediately on the screen after the upload completes, like SendSpace does?",
  "response": "There can be several reasons why WeTransfer doesn't immediately display shared file links on the screen after the upload completes, unlike SendSpace:\n\n1. **Verification Process**: WeTransfer may have additional verification processes to ensure the integrity and security of the uploaded files. This can take a few extra moments and may prevent immediate link generation.\n\n2. **User Experience Design**: The user interface and experience design choices made by WeTransfer might prioritize a different flow. They might be working on presenting the data in a more user-friendly or organized manner which might cause slight delays in showing the links.\n\n3. **Backend Processing**: WeTransfer could have backend processing steps that take additional time, such as organizing files, generating secure links, and preparing them for sharing. This processing ensures that the links are reliable and safe.\n\n4. **Scalability and Load Management**: Different services handle large volumes of data and user requests differently. WeTransfer may have built-in processes to manage and distribute load effectively which may delay the immediate display of shared links.\n\n5. **Feature Prioritization**: Companies prioritize and implement features based on their user feedback, technical capabilities, and product roadmap. WeTransfer might have different priority for immediate link sharing compared to SendSpace.\n\nThat said, user feedback is always valuable, and services often evolve and improve based on user needs and competitive benchmarking. If this is something users frequently request, WeTransfer might consider updating its processes in the future.",
